    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1504.02842v1</id>
    <title>Definition and Research of Internet Neurology</title>
    <updated>2015-04-11T06:17:58Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1504.02842v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/1504.02842v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>More and more scientific research shows that there is a close correlation between the Internet and brain science. This paper presents the idea of establishing the Internet neurology, which means to make a cross-contrast between the two in terms of physiology and psychology, so that a complete infrastructure system of the Internet is established, predicting the development trend of the Internet in the future as well as the brain structure and operation mechanism, and providing theoretical support for the generation principle of intelligence, cognition and emotion. It also proposes the viewpoint that the Internet can be divided into Internet neurophysiology, Internet neuropsychology, Brain Internet physiology, Brain Internet psychology and the Internet in cognitive science.</summary>
